DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,9,1);
$p = random(4,15,1);


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Use part I of the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus to
find the derivative of
\[ g(y) = \int_{$a}^{y} {t^{$p} \sin t}\, dt \]
$BR \( g'(y) \) = \{ans_rule( 20)\} $BR
[NOTE:  Enter a function as your answer.  Make sure that your
syntax is correct, i.e. remember to put all the necessary (, ), etc. ]
EOT

@ans=(fun_cmp("y^($p)*sin(y)", vars=>"y"));

ANS(@ans);

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

